    <h1>The api</h1>
    <p>The api allows you to utilize some of PhoenixBot's features in your own service. Below is the documentation for the api.</p>
    <p class="warning rounded-3"><span>&#9888;</span> These settings can only be set in a server with PhoenixBot. You cannot set it with the api at this time.</p>
    <h2>UserDB</h2>
    <p>Displays some useful info about yourself like your current time and pronouns.</p>
    <p>When using the api, replace [id] with the user's id. Don't include brackets in the url either.</p>
    <h3><span id="get">GET</span> /api/profile/[id]</h3>
    <p>Returns the whole profile of a user.</p>
    <h3><span id="get">GET</span> /api/pronouns/[id]</h3>
    <p>Returns the pronouns of a user.</p>
    <h3><span id="get">GET</span> /api/timefor/[id]</h3>
    <p>Sends a user's current time.</p>
    <h3><span id="get">GET</span> /api/socials/[id]</h3>
    <p>Returns the social media handles of a user.</p>
